  "texts": [
    "We constructed (and released) the first Arabic dataset, AuSTR, for that task using a language-independent approach, which we share to encourage the construction of similar datasets in other languages.",
    "Due to the relatively limited size of our dataset, we explored the adequacy of existing Arabic datasets of stance towards claims in training models for our task and the effect of augmenting our data with those datasets.",
    "Moreover, we tackled the class-imbalance issue by incorporating variant loss functions into our BERT-based stance model.",
    "Our experimental results suggest that adopting existing stance datasets is somewhat useful but clearly insufficient for detecting the stance of authorities.",
    "Moreover, when augmenting AuSTR with existing stance datasets, only the model trained with AuSTR augmented with AraStance outperformed the model trained with AuSTR solely, except on detecting the debunking tweets."
  ],
